==Set items==
===[[Leather]]===
[[Leather armour]] is good for beginning [[Ranged|rangers]]. They are very cheap and can also be [[Crafting|crafted]]. It comes in three types:

*[[Leather armour|Soft leather armour]] - no level requirements
**{{plink|Leather cowl}}
**{{plink|Leather body}}
**{{plink|Leather chaps}}
**{{plink|Leather gloves}}
**{{plink|Leather vambraces}}
**{{plink|Spiky vambraces}} - have the same stats as leather vambraces, aside from a small +2 [[Strength]] bonus (members only)
**{{plink|Leather boots}}
*[[Hard leather armour]] - level 10 [[Defence]]
**{{plink|Hardleather body}}
**{{plink|Hard leather shield}} - additional level 20 Ranged requirement
*[[Studded leather armour]] - level 20 Ranged
**{{plink|Coif}} - is often used with higher level sets
**{{plink|Studded body}} - additional level 20 Defence requirement
**{{plink|Studded chaps}}

===[[Frog-leather armour]]===
[[Frog-leather armour]] is only available to [[members]]. Players must have level 25 [[Ranged]] and level 25 [[Defence]] to wear this armour. Frog-leather armour is made by the [[Dorgeshuun]] [[goblin]]s. This armour is bought from [[Reldak]] in [[Dorgesh-Kaan]].

*{{plink|Frog-leather body}}
*{{plink|Frog-leather chaps}}
*{{plink|Frog-leather boots}}

===[[Snakeskin]]===
[[Snakeskin armour]] is only available to [[members]]. Players must have level 30 [[Ranged]] and level 30 [[Defence]] to wear this armour. Snakeskin armour can be made through the [[Crafting]] skill from [[snakeskin]], which can be obtained by killing [[snake]]s that appear in the [[Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup]], [[Temple Trekking]] [[minigame]]s or by killing snakes at [[Mos Le'Harmless]] Island.

The whole snakeskin set is hardly worn by [[Ranged|ranger]]s due to the huge amount of snakeskin hides needed. However, the [[Snakeskin boots]] and [[Snakeskin bandana|bandana]] offer most rangers a much cheaper alternative to the highly-priced [[Ranger boots]] and [[Robin hood hat]].

*{{plink|Snakeskin bandana}}
*{{plink|Snakeskin body}}
*{{plink|Snakeskin chaps}}
*{{plink|Snakeskin vambraces}}
*{{plink|Snakeskin boots}}
*{{plink|Snakeskin shield}}

===[[Spined armour]]===
[[Spined armour]] is only available for [[members]] and is [[Fremennik]] armour for [[Ranged|rangers]]. Players must complete [[The Fremennik Trials]] in order to equip the [[Spined body|body]], [[Spined legs|legs]], and [[Spined helm|helm]]. The helm, body, and chaps provide a slight Ranged attack bonus, and have an equip requirement of level 40 [[Ranged]] and [[Defence]]. Spined armour '''cannot''' be bought from stores and instead has to be earned from drops by the [[Dagannoth]]s under [[Waterbirth Island]]. Alternatively, the raw materials can be traded to [[Sigli the Huntsman]], who will create the armour for the player.

*{{plink|Spined helm}}
*{{plink|Spined body}}
*{{plink|Spined chaps}}
*{{plink|Spined gloves}}
*{{plink|Spined boots}}

===[[Ranger kit]]===
Obtained through only completing [[Clue scroll (medium)|medium]], [[Clue scroll (hard)|hard]], and [[Clue scroll (elite)|elite clue scrolls]]. 40 Ranged is required to wear them, with no Defence requirement. Aside from the [[Ranger boots]], these are generally unused among players as there are better alternatives. However the [[Rangers' tunic]] and [[Robin hood hat]] are popular among [[One-defence pure|1 Defence pures]] as they provide the highest Ranged bonus without requiring a Defence level.

*{{plink|Robin hood hat}}
*{{plink|Rangers' tunic}}
*{{Plink|Rangers' tights}}
*{{plink|Ranger gloves}}
*{{plink|Ranger boots}}

===[[Dragonhide]]===
[[Dragonhide armour]] is the most popular and the recommended armour players wear when [[ranging]]. [[Free players]] can only wear [[green dragonhide armour]], and must complete the [[Dragon Slayer I]] quest to wear the [[Green d'hide body|body]]. [[Blue dragonhide armour|Blue]], [[Red dragonhide armour|red]], and [[Black dragonhide armour|black dragonhides]] are only available to [[members]]. Members can also [[craft]] dragonhide armour. Trimmed and gold-trimmed versions on green and blue dragonhide armour have the same stats as normal. Trimmed versions '''cannot''' be crafted. They can only be obtained through [[clue scrolls]].

====[[Green dragonhide armour|Green dragonhide]]====
Players must have level 40 [[Ranged]] to wear this armour, along with an additional 40 [[Defence]] to wear the body and shield.
*{{plink|Green d'hide body}}
*{{plink|Green d'hide chaps}}
*{{plink|Green d'hide vambraces}}
*{{plink|Green d'hide shield}}

====[[Blue dragonhide armour|Blue dragonhide]]====
Players must have level 50 [[Ranged]] to wear this armour, along with an additional 40 [[Defence]] to wear the body and shield.
*{{plink|Blue d'hide body}}
*{{plink|Blue d'hide chaps}}
*{{plink|Blue d'hide vambraces}}
*{{plink|Blue d'hide shield}}

====[[Red d'hide armour|Red dragonhide]]====
Players must have level 60 [[Ranged]] to wear this armour, along with an additional 40 [[Defence]] to wear the body and shield.
*{{plink|Red d'hide body}}
*{{plink|Red d'hide chaps}}
*{{plink|Red d'hide vambraces}}
*{{plink|Red d'hide shield}}

====[[Black dragonhide armour|Black dragonhide]]====
Players must have level 70 [[Ranged]] to wear this armour, along with an additional 40 [[Defence]] to wear the body and shield.
*{{plink|Black d'hide body}}
*{{plink|Black d'hide chaps}}
*{{plink|Black d'hide vambraces}}
*{{plink|Black d'hide shield}}

====[[Blessed dragonhide armour|Blessed dragonhide]]====
There are six types of [[Blessed dragonhide armour|Blessed d'hide armour]], each representing the six [[gods]] - [[Guthix]] ([[Guthix blessed d'hide armour|green]]), [[Saradomin]] ([[Saradomin blessed d'hide armour|blue]]), [[Zamorak]] ([[Zamorak blessed d'hide armour|red]]), [[Armadyl]] ([[Armadyl blessed d'hide armour|white]]), [[Bandos]] ([[Bandos blessed d'hide armour|brown]]), and [[Ancient]] ([[Ancient blessed d'hide armour|purple]]). The armour has a +1 [[Prayer]] bonus on each piece, and offers improved bonuses over black dragonhide armour. All pieces require 70 [[Ranged]] and level 40 [[Defence]] except for [[blessed bracers]] and [[blessed chaps]], which only require 70 Ranged.

*{{plink|Blessed coif|pic=Guthix coif}}
*{{plink|Blessed body|pic=Guthix d'hide body}}
*{{plink|Blessed chaps|pic=Guthix chaps}}
*{{plink|Blessed bracers|pic=Guthix bracers}}
*{{plink|Blessed boots|pic=Guthix d'hide boots}}
*{{plink|Blessed shield|pic=Guthix d'hide shield}}

===[[Void Knight equipment]]===
[[Void Knight equipment]] is obtained from playing the [[Pest Control]] [[minigames|minigame]]. It requires 42 [[Attack]], [[Strength]], [[Defence]], [[Hitpoints]], [[Ranged]], and [[Magic]] along with 22 [[Prayer]] to buy and wear, for a total of 850 [[Void Knight commendation points]] points. When the full set is worn with a [[Void ranger helm]], it increases Ranged accuracy and damage by 10%.

Some players find it more effective to wear other Ranged armour such as [[Karil the Tainted's equipment|Karil's]] or [[Armadyl armour]] due to the superior accuracy and defence bonuses. However where accuracy is not an issue, Void knight equipment performs better due to the increase of damage.

The set effect bonus also stacks with the [[salve amulet(i)]]/[[salve amulet(ei)]] and [[Dragon hunter crossbow]] damage bonuses, making it a popular choice for fighting [[Vorkath]].

Additionally, it [[Combat styles|classes]] as a [[hybrid]] set, and as such gives equal Magic, Ranged and [[Melee]] Defence, thus making it an alternative choice when needing to use multiple combat styles.

*{{plink|Void ranger helm}}
*{{plink|Void knight top}}
*{{plink|Void knight robe}}
*{{plink|Void knight gloves}}

====[[Elite Void Knight equipment]]====
After completion of the [[Hard Western Provinces Diary]], players can upgrade their Void knight top and robe for 200 Pest Control points each, totalling 400 points. This enhances the set effect by 2.5% in accuracy and damage, totalling 12.5%. The elite pieces also provide a Prayer bonus; the other bonuses remain unchanged.

*{{plink|Elite void top}}
*{{plink|Elite void robe}}

===[[Crystal armour|Crystal]]===
[[Crystal armour]] can be obtained by combining [[crystal armour seed]]s with [[crystal shard]]s. after completing [[Song of the Elves]]. It degrades, requiring more crystal shards to recharge. Each piece provides a damage and accuracy bonus to the [[crystal bow]] and [[bow of Faerdhinen]]; equipping the full set confers an even greater buff. It requires 70 Defence to wear; 60 Ranged is also required to complete [[Mourning's End Part I]], a prerequisite quest for Song of the Elves.

*{{plink|Crystal helm}}
*{{plink|Crystal body}}
*{{plink|Crystal legs}}

===[[3rd age range equipment|3rd age]]===
[[3rd age range equipment]] is high level [[Ranged]] armour, and currently the second best non-degradable Ranged armour (just like its [[Melee]] and [[Magic]] counterparts). 3rd age range armour can be obtained as a very rare reward from [[Clue scroll (hard)|hard]], [[Clue scroll (elite)|elite]] and [[Clue scroll (master)|master clue scrolls]]. 3rd age range armour is supposedly made from white [[dragonhide]]. It requires 65 Ranged and 45 [[Defence]] to wear.

*{{plink|3rd age range coif}}
*{{plink|3rd age range top}}
*{{plink|3rd age range legs}}
*{{plink|3rd age vambraces}}

===[[Karil the Tainted's equipment|Karil's set]]===
[[Karil the Tainted's equipment|Karil the Tainted's set]] is high level [[degradable]] [[Ranged]] equipment, obtained as a possible reward from the [[Barrows]] [[minigames|minigame]]. When a player equips the entire set (including [[Karil's crossbow]]), attacks have a chance of reducing the opponent's [[Agility]] level during [[Player killing|PvP]] combat. If an [[amulet of the damned]] is worn alongside the set, when the effect activates, it inflicts an extra hitsplat, dealing more damage. It requires level 70 Ranged and [[Defence]] to wear.

*{{plink|Karil's coif}}
*{{plink|Karil's leathertop}}
*{{plink|Karil's leatherskirt}}

===[[Armadyl armour|Armadyl]]===
[[Armadyl armour]] is high level [[Ranged]] armour, offering some of the best attack and defence bonuses available to Ranged users. It is dropped by [[Kree'arra]] and his three bodyguards in the [[God Wars Dungeon]]. It requires level 70 Ranged and [[Defence]] to wear.

*{{plink|Armadyl helmet}}
*{{plink|Armadyl chestplate}}
*{{plink|Armadyl chainskirt}}

